#Lyrics
Jesus, in Thy dying woes, Even while Thy life-blood flows, Craving pardon for Thy foes: Hear us, holy Jesu.  2. Savior, for our pardon sue, When our sins Thy pangs renew, For we know not what we do: Hear us, holy Jesu.  3. Oh, may we, who mercy need, Be like Thee in heart and deed, When with wrong our spirits bleed: Hear us, holy Jesu.  4. Jesus, pitying the sighs Of the thief who near Thee dies, Promising him paradise: Hear us, holy Jesu.  5. May we in our guilt and shame Still Thy love and mercy claim, Calling humbly on Thy name: Hear us, holy Jesu.  6. May our hearts to Thee incline, Let us trust Thy grace divine, And with this poor thief be Thine: Hear us, holy Jesu.  7. Jesus, loving to the end Her whose heart Thy sorrows rend, And Thy dearest human friend: Hear us, holy Jesu.  8. May we in Thy sorrows share, And for Thee all peril dare, And enjoy Thy tenderest care: Hear us, holy Jesu.  9. May we all Thy loved ones be, All one holy family, Loving, for the love of Thee: Hear us, holy Jesu.  10. Jesus, whelmed in fears unknown, With our evil left alone, While no light from heav'n is shown: Hear us, holy Jesu.  11. When we seem in darkness lost, Shadow-stricken, tempest-tossed, Let not faith and hope be crossed: Hear us, holy Jesu.  12. May we never feel forsaken, Never let our trust be shaken, But with holy courage taken: Hear us, holy Jesu.  13. Jesus, in Thy thirst and pain, While Thy wounds the life-blood drain, Thirsting more our love to gain: Hear us, holy Jesu.  14. Thirst for us in mercy still, All Thy holy work fulfill, Satisfy Thy loving will: Hear us, holy Jesu.  15. May we thirst Thy love to know, Lead us in Thy ways below, To the founts of life to go: Hear us, holy Jesu.  16. Jesus, all our ransom paid, All Thy Father's will obeyed, By Thy suff'rings perfect made: Hear us, holy Jesu.  17. Save us in our soul's distress, Be our help to cheer and bless, While we grow in holiness: Hear us, holy Jesu.  18. Brighten all our heav'nward way With an ever holier ray, Till we pass to endless day: Hear us, holy Jesu.  19. Jesus, all Thy labor vast, All Thy woe and conflict past, Yielding up Thy soul at last: Hear us, holy Jesu.  20. When the death-shades round us lower, Guard us from the tempter's power, Keep us in that trial hour: Hear us, holy Jesu.  21. May Thy life and death supply Grace to live and grace to die, Grace to reach the home on high: Hear us, holy Jesu.

#Citations and References

Words: Thomas Benson Pollock, 1871 ("Metrical Litanies for Special Services and Ordinary Occasions"). A seven-part litany on the Seven Last Words of Christ; 21 stanzas in seven groups of three, one group for each word. Each stanza closes with the congregational response "Hear us, holy Jesu."
Music: 'Words on the Cross - The Litany' William Henry Monk, 1889.
Setting: "A Hymnal" (Episcopal), 1916, Hymn 164.
copyright: public domain. Pollock (d. 1896); Monk (d. 1889); pub. 1871/1916.

